solutions.content:
This [stackover flow post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1878001/how-do-i-check-if-a-c-stdstring-starts-with-a-certain-string-and-convert-a) descrives how to you ```string::rfind``` to implement ```startsWith```, which leads to following over all code to solve to problem.

```
int countPrefixes(const vector<string>& ws, const string& s) {
    return count_if(begin(ws), end(ws), [&](const string& w) { return s.rfind(w, 0) == 0; });
}
```

One might was well could use ```string::compare``` to solve the problem as well:

```
int countPrefixes(const vector<string>& ws, const string& s) {
    return count_if(begin(ws), end(ws), [&](const string& w) {
        return s.compare(0, size(w), w) == 0;
    });
}
```

